WEBVTT

00:01.129 --> 00:03.140
[theme music]

00:05.089 --> 00:08.140
(male narrator)
Long, long ago,
deep in the forest

00:08.160 --> 00:12.099
there was a hidden village
where tiny creatures lived.

00:12.119 --> 00:15.009
They called themselves Smurfs.

00:15.029 --> 00:17.050
They were good.

00:17.070 --> 00:19.019
[music continues]

00:22.120 --> 00:24.129
Then there was Gargamel

00:24.149 --> 00:27.219
the evil wizard.
He was bad.

00:28.000 --> 00:30.050
Ooh! I hate Smurfs!

00:31.129 --> 00:34.020
I'll get you,
I'll get all of you

00:34.039 --> 00:36.100
if it's the last thing
I ever do.

00:36.119 --> 00:38.070
[evil laugh]

00:38.090 --> 00:39.140
[Gargamel grunts]

00:39.159 --> 00:41.130
[grunting]
Oh! I'll get you.

00:41.149 --> 00:44.229
I'll find your village someday.
You'll be sorry.

00:45.009 --> 00:47.030
(male narrator)
Well, the forest is still there

00:47.049 --> 00:51.070
and if you listen,
you may here Gargamel's rage.

00:51.090 --> 00:54.060
And if you are good,
you may just catch

00:54.079 --> 00:57.030
a glimpse of the Smurfs.

00:59.179 --> 01:02.070
[theme music]

01:06.099 --> 01:08.099
[Gargamel laughing]

01:08.120 --> 01:11.099
It's nearly done, Azrael.

01:11.120 --> 01:13.140
[yawns]

01:13.159 --> 01:19.049
Behold, Azrael.
My latest stroke of evil genius.

01:19.069 --> 01:21.069
boom

01:21.090 --> 01:22.210
meow meow

01:22.230 --> 01:24.079
[sighs]

01:24.099 --> 01:25.180
This will turn me
into something

01:25.200 --> 01:28.069
those sniveling Smurfs
can't resist.

01:28.090 --> 01:30.039
[Gargamel cackles]

01:32.039 --> 01:34.000
[dramatic music]

01:34.020 --> 01:36.079
Ah, a smurfberry patch.

01:36.099 --> 01:39.210
Just the place to snare a Smurf.

01:42.039 --> 01:45.090
Now, a little bit of this.

01:47.099 --> 01:49.049
[music continues]

01:52.039 --> 01:54.099
[wailing]

01:54.120 --> 01:56.090
[humming]

01:58.079 --> 02:00.120
[baby crying]

02:00.140 --> 02:03.109
Oh, that sounded
just like a baby.

02:03.129 --> 02:05.180
But what's a baby
doing in the forest?

02:08.060 --> 02:10.169
[baby babbling]

02:10.189 --> 02:14.009
Oh, goodness me, a baby Smurf.

02:14.030 --> 02:17.110
Oh, where in the world
did you come from, huh?

02:17.129 --> 02:20.189
Oh, I bet you're hungry
as the dickens.

02:20.210 --> 02:23.090
I'll take you home
and feed you some yummy

02:23.110 --> 02:25.090
strained smurfberries.

02:25.110 --> 02:27.120
[babbling]

02:33.069 --> 02:37.180
Yoo-hoo, everybody. Yoo-hoo!
Look what I found in the forest.

02:37.199 --> 02:39.099
[clamoring]

02:40.229 --> 02:42.090
(Papa Smurf)
'A baby Smurf?'

02:42.110 --> 02:46.139
Where do baby Smurfs come from,
Brainy, huh, huh?

02:46.159 --> 02:50.090
Well, baby Smurfs
come from, uh..

02:50.110 --> 02:52.229
Well, this is certainly
a ridiculous question.

02:53.009 --> 02:56.180
Isn't he just the cutest thing
in the world?

02:56.199 --> 02:58.189
Cute? I don't think he's cute.

02:58.210 --> 03:02.039
I agree. In fact,
he's kind of ugly.

03:02.060 --> 03:04.080
[babbling]

03:04.099 --> 03:08.229
He is not ugly, Brainy.
He's just, well, unique-looking.

03:09.009 --> 03:11.039
Yes, he's certainly
not as smurfy as I am.

03:11.060 --> 03:15.060
But still, I must admit
he is unique-looking.

03:15.080 --> 03:17.069
Well, I think
he's very smurfy

03:17.090 --> 03:19.009
and I'm gonna
make him a present.

03:19.030 --> 03:21.060
Somebody say present?

03:21.079 --> 03:22.210
[chuckles]

03:22.229 --> 03:24.069
[Jokey gasps]

03:24.090 --> 03:25.139
[laughs]

03:26.189 --> 03:28.069
boom

03:29.180 --> 03:33.110
- I'll get some smurfberry jam.
- I've got an extra blanket.

03:33.129 --> 03:37.110
- I'll smurf some flowers.
- I hate baby Smurfs.

03:37.129 --> 03:38.219
[Smurfette grunts]

03:40.219 --> 03:43.009
Coochie coochie coo.

03:43.030 --> 03:45.079
[babbling]

03:45.099 --> 03:46.219
[Grouchy clears throat]

03:48.210 --> 03:51.189
(Smurfette)
Come, Baby Smurf. It's nap time.

03:51.210 --> 03:55.039
Now, I'll fix you some nice,
warm smurfberry juice.

03:55.060 --> 03:59.079
Smurfberry juice? Yuck!

03:59.099 --> 04:02.189
Hiya, Baby Smurf.
Look what I made for you.

04:02.210 --> 04:04.099
Pretty smurfy, huh?

04:10.080 --> 04:12.069
♪ Smurf-a-bye baby ♪

04:12.090 --> 04:14.000
♪ On the treetop ♪

04:14.020 --> 04:16.069
♪ When the wind blows
the cradle will.. ♪♪

04:16.089 --> 04:18.160
[crying]

04:18.180 --> 04:21.019
Hey, hey, don't cry,
please? Huh?

04:21.040 --> 04:23.199
Uh, I'll pick up the speed
a little, okay?

04:23.220 --> 04:28.019
- Oh, oh.
- Uh, hi, baby. Oof!

04:29.100 --> 04:31.139
[baby crying]

04:33.180 --> 04:37.209
- I can't stop it!
- I baked a cake for baby.

04:37.230 --> 04:40.090
[screams]

04:40.110 --> 04:41.209
Look out!

04:41.230 --> 04:43.040
plop

04:44.040 --> 04:46.170
Ooh, why you miserable..
I-I mean..

04:46.189 --> 04:49.100
[babbles]

04:49.120 --> 04:52.129
Hey, look at that.
He likes my cake.

04:52.149 --> 04:54.149
[instrumental music]

04:55.230 --> 04:58.060
You know, Grouchy,
there is something very familiar

04:58.079 --> 04:59.199
about this Baby Smurf.

05:03.199 --> 05:05.040
What is it about him?

05:07.040 --> 05:08.129
Coochie coo.

05:08.149 --> 05:11.209
Oh, don't touch me,
you wretched.. I-I-I mean..

05:11.230 --> 05:14.089
[babbles]

05:14.110 --> 05:16.019
Hmm, maybe I'll remember.

05:16.040 --> 05:19.139
Let's go, Grouchy.
Baby Smurf needs his rest.

05:22.110 --> 05:25.199
Oh, what's baby drinking?
No, no, no.

05:25.220 --> 05:28.129
What is this yuck?

05:28.149 --> 05:31.009
Oh, ick. It smells like poison.

05:31.029 --> 05:33.220
And poor baby almost drank it.

05:37.040 --> 05:39.139
Ooh, you empty-headed..
Uh, I mean..

05:39.159 --> 05:41.159
[babbling]

05:43.120 --> 05:45.040
[crickets chirping]

05:45.060 --> 05:48.060
[intense music]

05:52.060 --> 05:55.180
Baby Smurfs, Baby Smurfs,
nothing about..

05:55.199 --> 05:59.050
[yawns]
...Baby Smurfs.

06:02.009 --> 06:03.199
[snoring]

06:05.019 --> 06:06.209
[intense music]

06:08.100 --> 06:09.199
thud

06:18.000 --> 06:19.100
[grunts]

06:21.089 --> 06:25.000
Hmm. Aha!
Essence of wormwood.

06:25.019 --> 06:30.230
[cackles]
In a flash, I'll be my normal,
unlovable old self again.

06:31.009 --> 06:32.090
[shattering]

06:32.110 --> 06:34.110
What? Is some Smurf there?

06:34.129 --> 06:36.170
'What's smurfing on here?'

06:36.189 --> 06:40.120
Well, look at this. Who could
have smurfed such a mess?

06:40.139 --> 06:43.000
I thought I locked this cabinet.

06:43.019 --> 06:45.029
'There, that does it.'

06:46.209 --> 06:51.029
Oh, I must think of
something else. What's this?

06:51.050 --> 06:54.110
'Aha, the rare
cactus petrificus.'

06:54.129 --> 06:58.000
Now, that gives me
a most wicked idea.

07:00.019 --> 07:02.029
[humming]

07:03.180 --> 07:05.009
plop

07:05.029 --> 07:08.009
Good morning, Vanity.
Didn't you hear me, Vanity?

07:08.029 --> 07:09.060
I said, good morning.

07:09.079 --> 07:12.230
And I think it's extremely rude
not to..

07:13.009 --> 07:14.040
Vanity?

07:14.060 --> 07:15.230
[Baby Smurf laughing]

07:16.009 --> 07:19.069
[grunting]
One, two, three.

07:20.189 --> 07:22.079
Hefty, did you hear
what happened

07:22.100 --> 07:25.079
to Vanity and Brainy?
They're..

07:25.100 --> 07:27.149
[gasps]
Petrified!

07:27.170 --> 07:29.129
What's smurfing on around here?

07:29.149 --> 07:31.199
I don't know,
but I don't wanna catch it.

07:31.220 --> 07:36.050
But it inspires me to write
"An Ode to Petrification."

07:36.069 --> 07:39.170
To stand still
atop a windy hill..

07:39.189 --> 07:44.009
[stammering]
Maybe I'll change that to
"An Ode to Getting Out of Here."

07:44.029 --> 07:45.129
[intense music]

07:45.149 --> 07:47.009
splash

07:51.060 --> 07:55.079
Oh, boo-hoo. Papa Smurf,
something terrible has happened!

07:55.100 --> 07:56.139
What's wrong, Smurfette?

07:56.159 --> 07:58.079
Some awful, terrible thing

07:58.100 --> 08:00.129
is turning
all the Smurfs to stone.

08:00.149 --> 08:04.050
To stone? Smurfies me.
Now what about Baby Smurf?

08:04.069 --> 08:08.050
(Smurfette)
'I don't know. I can't
find him anywhere. Boo-hoo!'

08:09.120 --> 08:11.139
Come on, let's get
to the bottom of this.

08:11.160 --> 08:12.180
plop plop

08:14.060 --> 08:16.160
These poor Smurfs.

08:16.180 --> 08:19.220
Quick, bring them to my lab.
I must find a cure.

08:22.019 --> 08:24.139
Great smurf!
Someone's been in here!

08:24.160 --> 08:27.199
Oh, no. My cactus petrificus!

08:27.220 --> 08:31.149
That's what's petrifying
my Smurfs. But who's doing it?

08:31.170 --> 08:33.159
[intense music]

08:37.009 --> 08:39.190
I hate petrified Smurfs.

08:42.039 --> 08:45.000
I hate runaway wheelbarrows too.

08:46.190 --> 08:48.019
crash

08:48.039 --> 08:49.169
Now what?

08:52.110 --> 08:55.059
At this rate,
it'll take years to petrify

08:55.080 --> 08:57.009
all these miserable Smurfs.

08:57.029 --> 09:00.059
I need a way
to-to blow them all up at once.

09:00.080 --> 09:02.179
That's it.
I'll blow them all up.

09:03.149 --> 09:05.190
[intense music]

09:12.000 --> 09:16.039
Soon this village will be
nothing but a pile of blue dirt.

09:16.059 --> 09:18.059
At precisely 7 o'clock

09:18.080 --> 09:20.230
'the sun will set
on these miserable Smurfs'

09:21.009 --> 09:22.220
for the last time.

09:24.110 --> 09:27.059
(Smurfette)
Baby Smurf. Where are you?

09:27.080 --> 09:32.019
- 'Oh, that meddling wench.'
- Baby.

09:34.009 --> 09:36.120
[snoring]

09:36.139 --> 09:38.149
Huh? What's that?

09:38.169 --> 09:42.039
'Oh, Baby Smurf.
What are you d-d-doing?'

09:42.059 --> 09:46.000
I'm blowing all you vile
little Smurfs to smithereens.

09:46.019 --> 09:47.120
[cackles]

09:47.139 --> 09:50.230
Gargamel! Help!
Let me out of here!

09:53.220 --> 09:55.139
[cackles]

09:57.070 --> 09:59.059
[music continues]

10:02.019 --> 10:06.009
- Yes, this should do it.
- Papa Smurf, baby's gone.

10:06.029 --> 10:09.110
Oh, boo-hoo.
We can't smurf him anywhere.

10:09.129 --> 10:11.149
All we found was this.

10:15.059 --> 10:19.169
Just as I suspected.
It was Baby Smurf all along.

10:19.190 --> 10:21.230
But he's just a baby.

10:22.009 --> 10:24.159
That wasn't a baby.
That was Gargamel.

10:24.179 --> 10:25.190
[both gasp]

10:25.210 --> 10:27.190
(both)
Gargamel?

10:28.230 --> 10:31.029
[music continues]

10:33.190 --> 10:35.169
[all groaning]

10:35.190 --> 10:38.090
Did we give every Smurf
the antidote?

10:38.110 --> 10:40.090
Oh, I think so, Papa Smurf.

10:40.110 --> 10:42.110
[music continues]

10:45.080 --> 10:47.100
It won't be long now.

10:47.120 --> 10:49.000
[cackles]

10:50.059 --> 10:53.009
- Did you hear?
- Baby is Gargamel.

10:53.029 --> 10:55.129
[indistinct chatter]

10:55.149 --> 10:57.210
"Ode to Petrification."

10:58.230 --> 11:01.070
Lazy. Papa Smurf!

11:05.139 --> 11:08.190
[yawns]
Papa Smurf, Baby's got a bomb.

11:08.210 --> 11:12.039
- A bomb? Baby smurfed a bomb?
- Mm-hm.

11:12.059 --> 11:14.220
[yawns]
It's in the well.

11:15.000 --> 11:16.080
Here we go.

11:16.100 --> 11:17.110
[cackles]

11:17.129 --> 11:20.009
A few more seconds
and, kablooey

11:20.029 --> 11:21.149
'no more Smurfs.'

11:21.169 --> 11:26.009
[laughing]
Three, two, one, and presto.

11:28.139 --> 11:31.080
What happened
to that miserable bomb?

11:31.100 --> 11:33.169
[intense music]

11:35.230 --> 11:39.039
Badness me. Where's my bomb?

11:39.059 --> 11:40.159
Whoops!

11:40.179 --> 11:42.029
whoosh

11:44.039 --> 11:45.100
boom

11:45.120 --> 11:48.220
(Gargamel)
Ooh, I hate Smurfs!

11:49.000 --> 11:51.149
(all)
Bye-bye, Gargamel.

11:51.169 --> 11:54.149
swoosh

11:54.169 --> 11:55.179
crash

11:55.200 --> 11:57.029
meow

11:57.049 --> 11:59.220
Oh, well, home at last.

12:00.000 --> 12:03.149
Stay away from me,
you fool cat. Oh, no!

12:07.179 --> 12:09.110
[growling]

12:09.129 --> 12:13.159
Azrael, you numbskull,
it's me, Gargamel.

12:13.179 --> 12:15.000
Huh?

12:15.019 --> 12:16.159
[Azrael babbling]

12:18.000 --> 12:21.039
There it is.
My counter-spell. Ah.

12:22.139 --> 12:24.100
[instrumental music]

12:25.169 --> 12:27.090
What are you looking at?

12:30.059 --> 12:32.159
poof

12:32.179 --> 12:37.100
Azrael, you feline fool.
How dare you attack me?

12:37.120 --> 12:39.100
[meows]

12:39.120 --> 12:41.029
Oh, never mind.

12:41.049 --> 12:45.009
At least I don't have to look
like a disgusting Smurf anymore.

12:45.029 --> 12:46.110
How mortifying.

12:46.129 --> 12:49.029
Now, where did I put
those bad-luck charms?

12:49.049 --> 12:50.039
[Azrael laughing]

12:50.059 --> 12:51.120
Hmm, I can't find them.

12:51.139 --> 12:54.049
I thought I put them
over here. No, no.

12:58.230 --> 13:01.009
[theme music]
